\series bold 
Introduction
\series default 
 
\layout Standard

The magnetic field is the region surrounding a magnet in which forces due
 to the magnet are measurable.
 At a given point in the region, the strength of the field, similar to that
 of an electric field, is the force per unit north pole (one positive unit
 of magnetism), and the direction is indicated by the orientation of the
 north pole of a compass located at the point.
 On earth, the field mapped out around the magnet is actually the resultant
 of the field due to the magnet and the field due to the earth.
